'''Finn Surman''' (born 23 September 2003) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[central defender]] for the [[Portland Timbers]]. Born in Wales, he represents the [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand national team]].

==Club career==

=== Wellington Phoenix ===
In November 2021, Surman was one of three players who travelled to Australia to join [[Wellington Phoenix FC|Wellington Phoenix]]'s senior [[A-League Men]] side, forced to play away from home due to travel restrictions imposed due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://wellingtonphoenix.com/news/phoenix-men-call-in-reinforcements|title=Phoenix men call in reinforcements|date=30 November 2021|website=[[Wellington Phoenix FC]]|accessdate=18 April 2022}}</ref> He made his debut for the Phoenix in a win over [[Western United FC|Western United]] in the [[2021 FFA Cup]] on 7 December 2021.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/a-league/127219090/young-players-get-the-job-done-for-wellington-phoenix-men-in-the-ffa-cup|title=Young players get the job done for Wellington Phoenix men in the FFA Cup|first=Phillip|last=Rollo|date=8 December 2021|accessdate=20 April 2022|website=[[Stuff.co.nz]]}}</ref>

Surman signed a professional contract with the Phoenix in February 2022.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ftbl.com.au/news/nix-sign-teenage-duo-to-a-league-mens-side-576064|title=Nix sign teenage duo to A-League Men's side|date=16 February 2022|first=Ed|last=Jackson|access-date=20 April 2022|website=FTBL.com.au}}</ref> By April 2022, Surman was making regular appearances in the Phoenix's starting side.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/sport/football/a-league/128329787/wellington-phoenix-defender-finn-surman-wasnt-expecting-his-rise-to-be-so-rapid|first=Andrew|last=Voerman|website=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|access-date=20 April 2022|title=Wellington Phoenix defender Finn Surman wasn't expecting his rise to be so rapid}}</ref>

=== Portland Timbers ===
On 20 July 2024, Surman was transferred to [[Major League Soccer]] side [[Portland Timbers]] for an undisclosed fee. Surman was the third [[Wellington Phoenix FC Reserves|Wellington Phoenix]] academy graduate to sign an offshore club deal. Surman signed a contract through the 2026 season, with a club option till 2027.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timbers.com/news/timbers-sign-defender-finn-surman|title=Timbers Sign Defender Finn Surman|date=19 July 2024|access-date=19 July 2023|website=[[Portland Timbers]]}}</ref>

On 19 October 2024, Surman made his debut for the club, starting in a 1–1 draw against [[Seattle Sounders FC|Seattle Sounders]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Finn Surman|url=https://www.timbers.com/players/finn-surman/|website=Portland Timbers|access-date=2026-01-31|language=en|first=Portland|last=Timbers}}</ref>

==International career==
On 5 June 2023, he was called up by [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/129219|title=All Whites squad announced for games this month against Sweden and Qatar|date=5 June 2023|first=Ed|last=Jackson|access-date=10 June 2023|website=nzfootball.co.nz}}</ref>

He was also announced to represent the [[New Zealand men's national football team|All Whites]] in the [[2024 Summer Olympics|2024 Paris Olympics]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nzfootball.co.nz/newsarticle/143021?newsfeedId=1223399|title=Men's Football Team Announced for Paris 2024|date=10 July 2024|first=Ed|last=Jackson|access-date=19 July 2024|website=nzfootball.co.nz}}</ref>

